pan class=\"n\">divXPowOrder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>(<a href=\"https://github.com/bustercopley/mathlib4/commit/0e58f0e8238da6b8bc6de51ba072543ed04fa043\">commit</a>). The proof is by showing that <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=divXPowOrder#doc\">docs#divXPowOrder</a> is equal to a monoid homomorphism and using <code>map_pow</code>. It's a result I had need of, so it might be useful to someone else.</p>\n<p>OK to PR?</p>",
